Test Name:
User notification about third-party requests for user information

Criteria:
The company tells me if the government or other third parties ask for my information.

Indicators:
The company notifies users when government entities (including courts or other judicial bodies) request their user information.
The company notifies users when private parties request their user information.
The company clearly discloses situations when it might not notify users, including a description of the types of government requests it is prohibited by law from disclosing to users.
The company has a "warrant canary" (see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warrant_canary)

Procedure Overview:
Investigation and analysis of publicly available documentation to determine what the company clearly discloses.

Readiness Flag:
1
